<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-1348] Documentation of parameter &quot;argLine&quot; for goal &quot;surefire:test&quot; lacks mention of a key change made in v2.17</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1348</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The documentation for the argLine parameter &lt;a href=&quot;http://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-surefire-plugin/test-mojo.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; indicates &quot;since v2.1&quot; and the description refers to the @&lt;/p&gt;
{argLine} syntax but doesn&apos;t mention that you have to be using surefire-maven-plugin v2.17 or greater for that functionality to work. See &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1047&quot; title=&quot;Add @{...} property evaluation for the argLine&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SUREFIRE-1047&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SUREFIRE-1047&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; - Add @{...} property evaluation for the argLine&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Probably the &lt;a href=&quot;http://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-surefire-plugin/test-mojo.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;goal arguments page&lt;/a&gt; plus the FAQ page that it links to should be updated with a mention of the minimum required maven-surefire-plugin version.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I noticed this while experiencing issue &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1273&quot; title=&quot;Adding plugin inside Maven profile breaks mvn:build on project&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SUREFIRE-1273&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SUREFIRE-1273&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&quot;. Resolution of that issue should have been simple but I was on surefire-maven-plugin v2.12 and the documentation made it appear that @{argLine}
&lt;p&gt; was supported since v2.1. I needed to upgrade but there wasn&apos;t any obvious indication of that.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
